==English==
===Noun===
'''glasshouse''' (''plural'' '''glasshouses''')

# A building made of [[glass]] in which [[plant]]s are [[grow]]n more [[rapidly]] than outside such a building by the action of [[heat]] from the [[sun]], this heat being trapped inside by the glass. (chiefly commercial).
# A building where [[glass]] or [[glassware]] is manufactured.
# (''British army slang'') A military prison.

====Synonyms====
* [[greenhouse]] (chiefly domestic)

